mmary:\n\nPUBG's main website https://www.pubg.com has an endpoint that is vulnerable to an injection vulnerability - namely a reflected injection of JavaScript, also known as Reflected Cross Site Scripting (XSS). As per OWASP's definition: \"Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks are a type of injection, in which malicious scripts are injected into otherwise benign and trusted websites. \"\nThis happens because one of the GET parameters \"p\" does not properly sanitize/escape user input, allowing an injection to occur.\n\n## Steps To Reproduce:\n\nTo reproduce this, an attacker has to:\n\n  * Prepare a Javascript payload that it wants the victim to execute. In this case, for Proof of Concept purposes, our Javascript code will prompt an alert showing the users' cookies.\n\n```javascript\nalert(document.cookie);\n```\n\n  * Inject this Javascript code properly into the vulnerable parameter, creating thus a crafted future GET request that will inject the payload.\n\n```GETRequest\nGET /?p=iqz78'%3e%3cimg%20src%3da%20onerror%3dalert(document.cookie)%3d1%3echplq HTTP/1.1\nHost: www.pubg.com\nAccept-Encoding: gzip, deflate\nAccept: */*\nAccept-Language: en\nUser-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 9.0; Windows NT 6.1; Win64; x64; Trident/5.0)\nConnection: close\nReferer: https://www.pubg.com/es/feed/\nCookie: _icl_current_language=en; _icl_visitor_lang_js=en-us; wpml_browser_redirect_test=0; __cfduid=de74423d435717d651b1c9e2c63f4acc21575460678\n```\nRequest PoC {F651167}\n\n\n  * As this injection happens in a GET parameter, the attacker simply needs to send the crafted Link that produces this GET request to the victim and have the victim click it.\n\nInjection Demonstration {F651168}\n\n\n\n## Supporting Material/References:\n\n  * Video Demonstration\n\n{F651177}\n\n## Impact\n\nWith user interaction, an attacker could execute arbitrary Javascript code in a victim's browser.\nThis would allow an attacker to unwillingly make a victim:\n\n* Perform any action in the identified endpoint\n* View any information that the user is able to view\n* Modify any information that the user is able to modify (not sure if applicable in this case)\n* Interact with other application users as if it were him - impersonation (not sure if applicable in this case)","weakness":{"id":61,"name":"Cross-site Scripting (XSS) - Reflected"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":651167,"file_name":"request_poc2.png","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/mBrW1kCKcg3mqAniUzWqDhn3?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22request_poc2.png%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27request_poc2.png\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fpng\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQ444T3KV3%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T091303Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECkaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJGMEQCICNXcE2oMmBYdARsjSreiX1D5a8ULSJgK6YPAHUFFhJxAiB3Kama7K3S1H1145w5nAlyvmvoyp0La0v7qeVKNZup7iq6BQjy%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F8BEAMaDDAxMzYxOTI3NDg0OSIMMTR8dCXTX9reP0OQKo4FiIL2gaObt5JOvIfvAtpmoYSU3O23m9uxGyzGEBKxCqJpX5jeUbgbK3Jr5I3P3M21G4cCgKAT3n1Ee3xfx7AwI47mLVm9Qfbi9iyaVHtrnluZ4HZL6fdHIE2fX7i5jEnf%2FittRWoU1nQFL9oO7Yr5pe4ITYIK2e5hYNjSoDhUYNpSaR7%2B45QcqerkrIzbr1dItUmMP5RiDX%2Byuuh66jonF0b%2Fwr8Pl%2FQvGFMjiIKLQOXtQJ0%2FEo8Pj3Q3TIm5H298gjwabRHEwNxCe99UwSrdAcQ2GdKWQOtD3Dne6hoQ4Nq1exr5xXlBC%2BNHGKuOIxcuor0YUrRi96F%2BQrFPsW5nXQ%2Fdz6K5BNr%2Fuh1EscZMirAv7SsDB8gwOwYbzCI8tUzldrGp8l0fEBMqiS4fCJjeqRkq1yKL3cu4DLs4sNOYQYRCAzbKvpqGpXf%2FawCxERSgLukyci23ltc7h21z9EGEU0PMtYwa%2FlJiPpTVIUBB0XrqNIQPuN9PCMpCn811i7oIMXSVCqIhRhWvuAfwJWD0SFhVY9RUJO9EcAxroTsSleR%2F9HqtXDUtIHxM07IxU7%2BZ%2FgFuWc382hwCg6yQ8XbkPoyD8iMt%2FQQtE%2FEPwL3yYF2CfLtIomHXI1mRXmZlh8XVV6hpzr3O8sp6ojtfwCoyM2LppLIcWIf9vLniyY6AjwsSzjO9lNrhXjDECX2JBVZ5zue6x9VPQEbyvD9Hqq%2BUcrarI96PJHgAeqGQWRTLV74cU5DHyR%2FIp7jwKtA%2FSXyg6dG5Ua1W2u4cjfeAB9DCq8rUQidtTFU